It depends on, and is published separately from, the jammi_ai engine
(https://pypi.org/project/jammi_ai/, Apache-2.0). The cookbook imports jammi_ai
as a pinned dependency and contains no engine source.

Dataset attributions are recorded by the loaders that fetch them, in
jammi_cookbook/datasets.py and below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Datasets (fetched on demand, checksum-gated; not redistributed in this repo)

Air Routes
  Source: https://github.com/krlawrence/graph (sample-data), pinned to commit
    efd3b1ae636f602577cfbccb16ecfe358a02ee36 (graph version 0.89).
  Author: Kelvin R. Lawrence. Permissive use as published with the book
    "Practical Gremlin." Used here as a graph-construction/algorithms teaching set.

ogbn-arxiv
  Source: Open Graph Benchmark (https://ogb.stanford.edu/), arxiv.zip +
    titleabs.tsv.gz from snap.stanford.edu/ogb.
  License: ODC-BY 1.0 (Open Data Commons Attribution License). Built on the
    Microsoft Academic Graph. Citation: Hu et al., "Open Graph Benchmark:
    Datasets for Machine Learning on Graphs," NeurIPS 2020.

